hsrt.mec.controldeveloper.io

Interface IOType

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Console, ObjectFile, TextFile, WiFi

    public interface IOType
    Interface IOType defines the methods for reading and writing data into a data stream. The kind of data stream (e.g. keyboard, file, etc.) is defined in the class which implements this interface.

    The data from an input or output stream is provided by an object of type Vector.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description

      Closes the stream and releases any system resources associated with it.

    • Method Detail

      • read

        boolean read(Vector<String> content)
        Reads data from an input stream. The data is provided by the Vector object given as a parameter.
        Parameters:
        content - The vector in which the input data is written in a string format
        Returns:
        false, in case of an error; true, otherwise.

      • write

        boolean write(Vector<String> content)
        Writes data into an output stream
        Parameters:
        content - The vector that contains the output data in a string format
        Returns:
        false, in case of an error; true, otherwise.

      • close

        boolean close()
        Closes the stream and releases any system resources associated with it. Closing a previously closed stream has no effect.
        Returns:
        false, in case of an error; true, otherwise.
